cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about video generation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new loss function for GANs, which is related to machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Moreover, the paper deals with the challenge of memory and training stability, which is a common issue in multimedia (MM) research. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on an action recognition dataset, which is related to graphics (GR) research.
